cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF

This paper discusses network function virtualization (NFV) and its impact on network services. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses resource allocation and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper proposes an online algorithm, which involves control and decision-making, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The paper also discusses the profit-maximization problem, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a primal-dual based analysis, which falls under the category of cs.PF (Performance).
